       This chapter presents information users need to customize
       the appearance and behavior of icons.  Icons provide the
       user with a handy way to straighten up a cluttered
       workspace, and are a great tool for efficient multiprocess-   |
       ing.  Information is also presented on configuring the MWM
       icon box.  As a programmer, being aware of this information
       can help you avoid user-caused problems in your application.

       This chapter discusses the following topics:                  |

          +o Studying icon anatomy                                    |

          +o Manipulating icons                                       |

          +o Controlling icon appearance and behavior                 |

          +o Coloring icons                                           |

          +o Using the icon box to hold icons                         |

