       15.1.2  TTTThhhheeee LLLLaaaabbbbeeeellll

       The icon llllaaaabbbbeeeellll is a rectangle, located beneath the icon
       image, containing the name of the icon.  A label is usually   |
       supplied by the client (via the WM_ICON_NAME window pro-
       perty), but some clients, for example xxxxcccclllloooocccckkkk, provide a       |
       command-line option enabling you to write in your own label.

       Icon labels are truncated on the right to the width of the
       icon image when the icon is not active.  When the icon
       becomes active, the full text of the label appears.           |

